-- Hess Reports Hole in Pipeline Near Port Reading, New Jersey, Oil Refinery
-- Aaron Clark
-- 2010-09-20T14:25:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/hess-refinery-in-new-jersey-has-spill-into-waterway-through-hole-in-pipe.html

          
          
             Hess Corp.  reported a hole in a
pipe near its Port Reading, New Jersey,  refinery , according to a
filing with state regulators.  
 The hole resulted in a spill into the Arthur Kill waterway,
according to the Sept. 18 filing with the New Jersey Department
of Environmental Protection.  
 “This small release was related to dock piping at our
terminal so had no impact on our units or on production,” the
company said in an e-mailed statement.  
